observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed to:
a. Conduct regular evaluation of the money placement made in order to evaluate its viability and profitability;
b. Ensure that placement of funds in the time deposits undergo the process of identification described in the regulation and properly documented;
c. Consider terminating the placement of the funds in the time deposits and if found to be unrestricted or unappropriated, use the funds for the implementation of the Municipality’s programs, projects and activities or invest the funds in high-interest bearing instruments.

We recommended that Management:
a. Require the Municipal Accountant to regularly monitor the Accounts Payable account and ensure that all documents for claims are intact to ensure prompt settlement of the liabilities;
b. Confirm the existence of the accounts without records or supporting documents with the creditors and make the necessary adjustments based on the results of the confirmations; 
c. Draw a Journal Entry Voucher to correct the errors and/or misclassifications.

We recommended that Management:
a. Instruct the concerned Municipal Officials to closely monitor the implementation of identified projects funded from the said funds to prevent non-utilization thereof; 
b. Conduct a thorough evaluation of the programs relative to the unutilized funds and to revert the same to the source agency or to the national treasury if no longer needed pursuant to COA Circular No. 94-013; 
c. Confirm the existence of the accounts without records or supporting documents with the source agencies and make the necessary adjustments based on the results of the confirmations; 
d. Require the Municipal Accountant to draw a Journal Entry Voucher to correct the errors and/or misclassifications in the aggregate amount of P1,843,883.05.

