We have recommended that the following:
a. In the event of failure of bidding, the BAC undertake the mandatory review and evaluation of the terms, conditions, and specifications in the bidding documents, so that the necessary revisions and/or adjustments could be made to avoid further failure of bidding;
b. The BAC see to it that the appropriate alternative mode of procurement is adopted when there is a failure of public bidding;
c. The municipality adhere strictly to the prescribed threshold for shopping and small value procurement as provided in the Revised IRR of RA No. 9184; and
d. The BAC make certain that in the evaluation of quotations/bids, contracts are awarded to suppliers whose quoted prices were within the ABC.
